HEADWORD: Bovey coal
<hw>Bo"vey coal`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A kind of
mineral coal, or brown lignite, burning with a weak flame, and generally
a disagreeable odor; -- found at <ets>Bovey</ets> Tracey, Devonshire,
England. It is of geological age of the o⟦oum⟧lite, and not of the true
coal era.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bovid</ent>⟦br⟧
